[project]
    dependencies = [
        "ray[data,serve,train,tune]==2.42.1",
        "transformers==4.49.0",
        "datasets==3.3.1",
        "torch==2.6.0+cpu",
        "aim>=3.27.0",
]
    description="Training framework"
    name="training"
    readme="README.md"
    requires-python="==3.12.*"
    version="0.1.0"

[tool.uv.sources]
torch = { index = "pytorch" }

[[tool.uv.index]]
url = "https://pypi.org/simple"

[[tool.uv.index]]
name = "pytorch"
url = "https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu"


[build-system]
    requires = ["hatchling"]
    build-backend = "hatchling.build"

FROM ubuntu:20.04
ARG TARGETPLATFORM

# Install required packages in a single layer
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    python3-pip \
    wget \
    curl \
    git \
    && apt-get clean \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Install Python packages in a separate layer
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir huggingface_hub datasets

RUN  ARCH=$(echo $TARGETPLATFORM | cut -d / -f 2) && \
    wget https://dl.min.io/client/mc/release/linux-${ARCH}/mc \
    && chmod +x mc \
    && mv mc /usr/local/bin/

# Default command when container starts
CMD ["/bin/bash"]

FROM aisiom/rayproject-ray:2.42.1-py312-cpu

# Set environment variables
ENV PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=true

RUN pip install torch==2.6.0+cpu --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu \
    && pip install \
    transformers==4.49.0 \
    datasets==3.3.1 \
    aim==3.27.0 \
    && rm -rf ~/.cache/pip

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: aim-runs-claim
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany
  storageClassName: "nfs" 
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 100Mi

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  labels:
    app: aim-deployment
  name: aim-deployment
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: aim-deployment
  strategy:
    rollingUpdate:
      maxSurge: 25%
      maxUnavailable: 25%
    type: RollingUpdate
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: aim-deployment
    spec:
      containers:
      - image: aimstack/aim:latest
        name: aim-deployment
        command: ["aim"]
        args: ["up", "--repo", "/aim"]
        ports:
          - containerPort: 43800
            protocol: TCP
        resources:
          limits:
            cpu: 0.5
            memory: 1Gi
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 1Gi
        volumeMounts:
          - mountPath: /aim
            name: aim-runs
      volumes:
        - name: aim-runs
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: aim-runs-claim
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: aim
spec:
  selector:
    app: aim-deployment
  ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 80
      targetPort: 43800

apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: stanfordnlp-imdb-dataset-sync
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: dataset-sync
        image: localhost:5001/job:{{ .Values.environment }}
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        command:
        - /bin/bash
        - -c
        - |
          # Configure MinIO client
          mc alias set myminio http://minio.minio-internal-{{ .Values.environment }}.svc.cluster.local:9000 $MINIO_ACCESS_KEY $MINIO_SECRET_KEY

          # Create bucket if it doesn't exist
          mc mb myminio/datasets --ignore-existing

          # Create temporary directory for dataset
          mkdir -p /tmp/dataset

          # Download dataset from Hugging Face and save to disk
          python3 -c "from datasets import load_dataset; dataset = load_dataset('stanfordnlp/imdb'); dataset.save_to_disk('/tmp/dataset')"

          # Upload to MinIO
          mc cp -r /tmp/dataset/ myminio/datasets/imdb/

          # Cleanup
          rm -rf /tmp/dataset
        env:
        - name: MINIO_ACCESS_KEY
          value: "minioadmin"
        - name: MINIO_SECRET_KEY
          value: "minioadmin"
        - name: ENVIRONMENT
          value: {{ .Values.environment }}
      restartPolicy: Never
  backoffLimit: 4
  activeDeadlineSeconds: 120  # Job will fail after 120 seconds if not completed

apiVersion: ray.io/v1
kind: RayCluster
metadata:
  name: {{ .Values.rayClusterName }}-{{ .Values.environment }}
spec:
  rayVersion: '2.42.1'
  enableInTreeAutoscaling: false
  headGroupSpec:
    serviceType: ClusterIP
    rayStartParams:
      dashboard-host: '0.0.0.0'
      block: 'true'
    template:
      spec:
        containers:
          - name: ray-head
            # This image will be built from the training.Dockerfile 
            image: localhost:5001/training:{{ .Values.environment }}
            imagePullPolicy: Always
            ports:
              - containerPort: 6379
                name: gcs
              - containerPort: 8265
                name: dashboard
              - containerPort: 10001
                name: client
            resources:
              limits:
                cpu: "4"
                memory: "8G"
              requests:
                cpu: "4"
                memory: "8G"
            volumeMounts:
              - mountPath: /tmp/ray
                name: ray-logs
              - mountPath: /aim
                name: aim-runs-volume
        volumes:
          - name: ray-logs
            emptyDir: {}
          - name: aim-runs-volume
            persistentVolumeClaim:
              claimName: aim-runs-claim
  workerGroupSpecs:
    - groupName: small-group
      replicas: 2
      minReplicas: 1
      maxReplicas: 3
      rayStartParams:
        block: 'true'
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
            - name: ray-worker
              # preloaded onto nodes
              image: localhost:5001/training:{{ .Values.environment }}
              imagePullPolicy: Always
              lifecycle:
                preStop:
                  exec:
                    command: ["/bin/sh","-c","ray stop"]
              resources:
                limits:
                  cpu: "2"
                  memory: "6G"
                requests:
                  cpu: "2"
                  memory: "6G"
              volumeMounts:
                - mountPath: /tmp/ray
                  name: ray-logs
                - mountPath: /aim
                  name: aim-runs-volume
          volumes:
            - name: ray-logs
              emptyDir: {}
            - name: aim-runs-volume
              persistentVolumeClaim:
                claimName: aim-runs-claim

apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: pythia-70m-model-sync
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: model-sync
        image: localhost:5001/job:{{ .Values.environment }}
        imagePullPolicy: Always
        command:
        - /bin/bash
        - -c
        - |
          # Configure MinIO client
          mc alias set myminio http://minio.minio-internal-{{ .Values.environment }}.svc.cluster.local:9000 $MINIO_ACCESS_KEY $MINIO_SECRET_KEY

          # Create bucket if it doesn't exist
          mc mb myminio/models --ignore-existing

          # Create temporary directory for model
          mkdir -p /tmp/model

          # Download model from Hugging Face
          huggingface-cli download EleutherAI/pythia-70m --local-dir /tmp/model --local-dir-use-symlinks False

          # Upload to MinIO
          mc cp -r /tmp/model/ myminio/models/pythia-70m/

          # Cleanup
          rm -rf /tmp/model
        env:
        - name: MINIO_ACCESS_KEY
          value: "minioadmin"
        - name: MINIO_SECRET_KEY
          value: "minioadmin"
        - name: ENVIRONMENT
          value: {{ .Values.environment }}
      restartPolicy: Never
  backoffLimit: 4
  activeDeadlineSeconds: 120  # Job will fail after 120 seconds if not completed

import os
import tempfile
from pathlib import Path
from tempfile import TemporaryDirectory

import pyarrow
import ray
import torch

# Import Aim
from aim import Run
from datasets import load_from_disk
from pyarrow.fs import S3FileSystem
from ray.train import RunConfig, ScalingConfig
from ray.train.torch import TorchTrainer, prepare_data_loader, prepare_model
from torch.nn.parallel import DistributedDataParallel
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader
from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer

runtime_env = {
    "env_vars": {
        "ENVIRONMENT": os.environ["ENVIRONMENT"],
    }
}

# Define the scaling configuration
scaling_config = ScalingConfig(
    num_workers=2,
    use_gpu=False,
    resources_per_worker={"CPU": 1, "memory": 4 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024},
)

# Training configuration
train_config = {
    "model_location": "pythia-70m",  # This is the path in MinIO under the models bucket
    "batch_size": 2,
    "learning_rate": 5e-5,
    "num_epochs": 1,
    "max_iterations": 10,
}


# For copying from S3 to local:
def copy_dir_from_s3(fs, source_path, target_path):
    file_info = fs.get_file_info(pyarrow.fs.FileSelector(source_path))
    for file in file_info:
        if file.type == pyarrow.fs.FileType.Directory:
            subdir = os.path.basename(file.path)
            os.makedirs(os.path.join(target_path, subdir), exist_ok=True)
            copy_dir_from_s3(fs, file.path, os.path.join(target_path, subdir))
        else:
            os.makedirs(target_path, exist_ok=True)
            with (
                fs.open_input_file(file.path) as s3_file,
                open(
                    os.path.join(target_path, os.path.basename(file.path)), "wb"
                ) as local_file,
            ):
                local_file.write(s3_file.read())


# For copying from local to S3:
def copy_dir_to_s3(fs, source_path, target_path):
    for root, _, files in os.walk(source_path):
        for file in files:
            local_path = os.path.join(root, file)
            relative_path = os.path.relpath(local_path, source_path)
            s3_path = os.path.join(target_path, relative_path)
            with (
                open(local_path, "rb") as local_file,
                fs.open_output_stream(s3_path) as s3_file,
            ):
                s3_file.write(local_file.read())


def train_func(config):
    # Get the current worker's rank
    rank = ray.train.get_context().get_world_rank()
    trial_id = ray.train.get_context().get_trial_id()

    # Initialize Aim Run - only on the main process (rank 0)
    if rank == 0:
        # Create an Aim run with the trial ID as experiment name
        aim_run = Run(experiment=f"sentiment_training_{trial_id}", repo="/aim")

        # Track configurations
        aim_run["hparams"] = {
            "model": config["model_location"],
            "batch_size": config["batch_size"],
            "learning_rate": config["learning_rate"],
            "num_epochs": config["num_epochs"],
            "max_iterations": config.get("max_iterations", "None"),
        }

    # Initialize the S3 filesystem
    fs = S3FileSystem(
        access_key="minioadmin",
        secret_key="minioadmin",  # noqa
        endpoint_override=f"minio.minio-internal-{os.environ['ENVIRONMENT']}.svc.cluster.local:9000",
        scheme="http",
    )

    # copy data to disk
    print("Copying data to disk")
    with TemporaryDirectory() as tmp_dir:
        imdb_path = Path(tmp_dir)
        copy_dir_from_s3(fs, "datasets/imdb/", imdb_path)
        print("Data copied to disk")

        # Load datasets
        train_dataset = load_from_disk(str(imdb_path / "train"))
        test_dataset = load_from_disk(str(imdb_path / "test"))

    # Take subset of data
    train_dataset = train_dataset.take(train_config["batch_size"])
    test_dataset = test_dataset.take(train_config["batch_size"])

    # Prepare local directory for the model files
    s3_path = f"models/{config['model_location']}/"

    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as local_model_dir:
        # Copy the model files from S3 to local directory
        print(f"Copying model files from {s3_path} to {local_model_dir}")
        copy_dir_from_s3(fs, s3_path, local_model_dir)
        print("Model files copied to local directory")

        # Initialize tokenizer and model from local directory
        tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(local_model_dir)
        if tokenizer.pad_token is None:
            tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token

        model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(
            local_model_dir, use_safetensors=True
        )
        model.gradient_checkpointing_enable()
        model.use_cache = False

        # Prepare the model for distributed training
        model = prepare_model(model)

        def preprocess_function(examples):
            prompts = [
                f"Review: {text}\nSentiment: {label}\n"
                for text, label in zip(examples["text"], examples["label"], strict=True)
            ]
            encoded = tokenizer(
                prompts, truncation=True, max_length=512, padding="max_length"
            )
            encoded["labels"] = encoded["input_ids"].copy()
            return encoded

        # Preprocess datasets
        tokenized_train = train_dataset.map(
            preprocess_function,
            batched=True,
            remove_columns=train_dataset.column_names,  # pyright: ignore
        )
        tokenized_test = test_dataset.map(
            preprocess_function,
            batched=True,
            remove_columns=test_dataset.column_names,  # pyright: ignore
        )

        # Convert to PyTorch datasets
        train_dataset = tokenized_train.with_format("torch")
        test_dataset = tokenized_test.with_format("torch")

        # Create DataLoaders
        train_loader = DataLoader(
            train_dataset, batch_size=config["batch_size"], shuffle=True
        )
        test_loader = DataLoader(
            test_dataset, batch_size=config["batch_size"], shuffle=False
        )

        # Prepare data loaders for distributed training
        train_loader = prepare_data_loader(train_loader)
        test_loader = prepare_data_loader(test_loader)

        # Training setup
        optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=config["learning_rate"])

        # Training loop
        model.train()
        epoch_loss = 0.0
        global_step = 0

        for epoch in range(config["num_epochs"]):
            epoch_loss = 0.0
            for batch_idx, batch in enumerate(train_loader):
                optimizer.zero_grad()

                # Forward pass
                outputs = model(**batch)
                loss = outputs.loss
                loss.backward()
                optimizer.step()

                epoch_loss += loss.item()
                global_step += 1

                # Log to Aim on rank 0
                if rank == 0:
                    aim_run.track(
                        loss.item(),
                        name="training_loss",
                        step=global_step,
                        context={"epoch": epoch, "batch": batch_idx},
                    )

                # Report metrics to Ray
                ray.train.report(
                    {"training_loss": loss.item(), "epoch": epoch, "step": global_step}
                )

                # Check if we've reached max iterations
                if (
                    config.get("max_iterations")
                    and global_step >= config["max_iterations"]
                ):
                    break

            # Evaluate on test set
            model.eval()
            test_loss = 0.0
            with torch.no_grad():
                for batch in test_loader:
                    outputs = model(**batch)
                    test_loss += outputs.loss.item()

            avg_test_loss = test_loss / len(test_loader)

            # Log to Aim on rank 0
            if rank == 0:
                aim_run.track(
                    avg_test_loss,
                    name="test_loss",
                    step=global_step,
                    context={"epoch": epoch},
                )

            model.train()

            # Report test loss
            ray.train.report(
                {"test_loss": avg_test_loss, "epoch": epoch, "step": global_step}
            )

            # Check if we've reached max iterations
            if config.get("max_iterations") and global_step >= config["max_iterations"]:
                break

        # Save the model on the main process
        if rank == 0:
            # Log model architecture to Aim
            aim_run["model_summary"] = str(model)

            # Save the model to local directory
            if isinstance(model, DistributedDataParallel):
                model.module.save_pretrained(local_model_dir)
            else:
                model.save_pretrained(local_model_dir)
            tokenizer.save_pretrained(local_model_dir)

            # Copy the saved model files back to S3
            checkpoint_path = f"models/checkpoints/sentiment_model/{trial_id}"
            copy_dir_to_s3(fs, local_model_dir, checkpoint_path)

            # Log the checkpoint path to Aim
            aim_run["checkpoint_path"] = checkpoint_path

            # End the Aim run
            aim_run.close()

    return {"final_loss": epoch_loss / len(train_loader), "global_step": global_step}


if __name__ == "__main__":
    # Run `make ray_port_forward` ahead of this to make the ray cluster accessible
    ray.init(address="ray://localhost:10001", runtime_env=runtime_env)

    with TemporaryDirectory() as results_dir:
        # Create the trainer
        trainer = TorchTrainer(
            train_func,
            train_loop_config=train_config,
            scaling_config=scaling_config,
            run_config=RunConfig(results_dir),
        )

    # Start training
    try:
        results = trainer.fit()
    finally:
        ray.shutdown()
